e central role of narrative in science and how models improve them. The book takes data and modeling seriously, with a sophisticated philosophy of science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEcologyxPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Ecology.2bisacsh1 aHoekstra, Thomas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/alle0691840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231538466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231538466.jpg  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles